parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "SLURM",
"details": {
"software": [
"Gromacs",
"Plumed",
"Intel",
"IMPI",
"MKL",
"Boost"
],
"resources": [
"CPU",
"Memory",
"Storage"
],
"modules": [
"intel/2020.1",
"impi/2018.4",
"mkl/2020.1",
"boost/1.75.0",
"plumed/2.8.0",
"gromacs/2021.4-plumed.2.8.0"
]
}
}
```

The script is using SLURM (Simple Linux Utility for Resource Management) to manage the execution of the simulation on a high-performance computing cluster. The script is running a Gromacs simulation with Plumed to analyze the trajectory data. The simulation is run on multiple nodes with specified CPU cores and memory allocation. 

The script loads various modules including Intel, IMPI, MKL, Boost, Plumed and Gromacs. These modules provide the necessary libraries and software for the simulation. 

The script uses Gromacs commands to extract and manipulate the trajectory data. The script also utilizes a custom script called `FN` (defined as the basename of the current working directory) to specify the output file name.
